         </div><div type="apparatus">
            <div type="textpart">
               <head xml:lang="eng">C. 127.1</head>
               <listApp><app loc="2"><lem>jaya<unclear>ti</unclear></lem><rdg source="bib:Finot1915_06">jayadā<supplied reason="lost">naṁ</supplied></rdg><note>This reading was repeated, without square brackets and introducing a new variation (<foreign>prakāśavarmmā</foreign>), in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Schweyer2009_01"/><citedRange unit="page">35, note 60</citedRange></bibl>.</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
         </div>
      <div type="translation">
         <div type="textpart">
            <head xml:lang="eng">C. 127.1</head><!-- AL: I removed <div type="textpart"> to try to get a left aligned head (as it was in C. 3. 2)--><p>Homage to Śiva. Śrī Prakāśadharmmā triumphs!</p>
         </div>
         <div type="textpart">
            <head xml:lang="eng">C. 127.2</head>
            <p>Lord of Campā.</p>
         </div>
         </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="fra">
         <div type="textpart">
         <head xml:lang="fra">C. 127.1</head><p>Hommage à Śiva. Śrī Prakāśadharmmā triomphe!</p>
         </div>
         <div type="textpart">
            <head xml:lang="fra">C. 127.2</head>
            <p>Seigneur du Campā.</p>
         </div>
      </div>
